                      <h2><a href="/religion-liberty/volume-33-number-1">Religion &amp; Liberty: Volume 33, Number 1</a></h2>
          
          <h1><span>Is Critical Race Theory un-American?</span>
</h1>
          <h3 class="byline">
                          by 
  
          <a href="/about/author/samuel-kronen" hreflang="en">Samuel Kronen</a>,
    
  
          <a href="/about/author/nate-hochman" hreflang="en">Nate Hochman</a>
    
  
 •
                        February 15, 2021
          </h3>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

          <div class="container container--featured-image-caption">
        <div class="featured-image__caption-wrapper">
                      <span class="featured-image__caption">
              
            <div class="field field--name-field-featured-image-caption field--type-string field--label-hidden field__item">A Black Lives Matter protester burns a flag outside the Multnomah County Courthouse in Portland, Oregon.</div>
      
            </span>
                                <span class="featured-image__credit">
              
            <div class="field field--name-field-featured-image-credit field--type-string field--label-hidden field__item"> (Photo credit: John Rudoff / Sipa USA via AP Images.)</div>
      
            </span>
                  </div>
      </div>
    
  </header>


<main class="main article article--religion-liberty" id="main-content">

  <article role="article" about="/religion-liberty/volume-33-number-1/critical-race-theory-un-american" class="node--type-ral-article">
    
    
    

    <div class="container">

              <div class="article__share">
          <div class="module connect connect--share">

  <div class="connect__description">
    Share this article:
  </div>

